If formula_265 is a normable space and if formula_301 is an absolutely summable family in formula_246 then necessarily all but a countable collection of formula_316’s are zero. Hence, in normed spaces, it is usually only ever necessary to consider series with countably many terms.

Summable families play an important role in the theory of nuclear spaces.

=== Series in Banach and seminormed spaces ===
