=== Examples ===
* Given a function formula_341 into an abelian topological group formula_342 define for every formula_343 formula_344 a function whose support is a singleton formula_345 Then formula_346 in the topology of pointwise convergence (that is, the sum is taken in the infinite product group formula_347).
* In the definition of partitions of unity, one constructs sums of functions over arbitrary index set formula_236 formula_349 While, formally, this requires a notion of sums of uncountable series, by construction there are, for every given formula_350 only finitely many nonzero terms in the sum, so issues regarding convergence of such sums do not arise. Actually, one usually assumes more: the family of functions is &quot;locally finite&quot;, that is, for every formula_200 there is a neighborhood of formula_200 in which all but a finite number of functions vanish. Any regularity property of the formula_353 such as continuity, differentiability, that is preserved under finite sums will be preserved for the sum of any subcollection of this family of functions.
* On the first uncountable ordinal formula_354 viewed as a topological space in the order topology, the constant function formula_355 given by formula_356 satisfies formula_357 (in other words, formula_354 copies of 1 is formula_354) only if one takes a limit over all &quot;countable&quot; partial sums, rather than finite partial sums. This space is not separable.

